President Uhuru Kenyatta on Friday issued a stern warning to the newly ap- pointed PSs and Chief Administrative Secretaries. He said they will be held responsible for any misuse of public resources. After witnessing the swearing-in of the top government officials at State House, Nairobi, the President said he will expect the highest standards of in- tegrity. “My decision today that the oath of office you have taken be accompanied by an Integrity and ethics code, both signed in public, is my demonstration of this commitment,” the President told them. He warned, “I want to repeat: No one will be spared if caught engaging in corruption and abuse of office. The law will take its due course.”  Click here for the latest political news 